@node "Bugs" "Know Bugs"
@{b}----------------------------------------------------------------------------
                          Music File System V1.56
                       (c)95/96/97/98   R.F.Bisschop
----------------------------------------------------------------------------@{ub}

Here are the know bugs in MFS:
------------------------------
*Pitch style sometimes gives 00 instead of 10, 12, 15, 17 or 20!
 I can't find the problem, tests reveal no problem!

*Contents printing:
 The centre button for artist/title/type etc. is off while is says 'on'
 please take note of this. Also, I don't know if any other printing
 part of MFS has the same problem. Some routines are used by multiple
 procedures!

*While printing you get a requester asking you for Yes (continue) or
 No (abort) please use keyboard Y/N to confirm since the mouse does
 not seem to work.

AmigaGuide
----------
Something strange happend when I tried to use a newer version
of Amigaguide.datatype (v40+) to display Menus.guide. It was not possible
for me to load the Index (Multiview locked up). I now use the old
datatype (V39) and everything works just as it should. You might want
to check out the 'Sys:Classes/Datatypes/' directory.

Kickstart 3.1
-------------
I can use kick 3.1 on my 3.0 machine by using the MapRom tool
of my Blizzard turbocard. I noticed that under this kickrom 3.1 a
MFS' Interlaced screen does NOT work correctly.
@endnode

