@node "HIST" "History"
@{b}----------------------------------------------------------------------------
                   The History Of The Music File System
----------------------------------------------------------------------------@{ub}

When I bought my first Amiga 500 (1987/Kick1.2/512kb) I wanted to do
something special and usefull with it. So I fooled around in Amiga Basic
and created the first version of MFS, which was called CDL (Compact Disc
List). Compared to this version it was quitte simple but the 'basics'
are still the same.
Later on in life I got my self a copy of Amos V1.0. I constructed a new
version of CDL, CDS (Compact Disc System). CDS reached version 7 and was
a nice program to work with. But I wanted more, I wanted something better.
So here is MFS. I been working on and off it for the last two years (1995).

Ps. Remember this : AMIGA, dE gROotStE fAmILie VaN NeDERLaNd !!

Computer used creating version 1.50
-----------------------------------
Amiga 1200, 2MB Chip/16MB Fast, Blizzard 1230-III + SCSI Kit,
3 Disk drives, 270 MB Harddisk, 1GB Iomega Jazz, Star LC24-10 printer
and 1084S Video Monitor. Optional Epson styles 600 printer.

Version 1.00 (01/01/1997)
-------------------------
Here's a list of some of the (major) new futures:
Upto 9999 albums. New medium type indicating (CD-SGL etc.). Support lots
of mediums now, not only CD's. Different screen mode support & auto detect.
Year, Label and Comment added. Multi file mode (and all it's functions).
Buffer size change. Workbench look. Extended configuration file.
Merge & split functions trou-out the program. You can add a sample now.
Sample player & Song player. Time calculator. Tape selection in a window.
Extended preferences. Extended Statistics and lots, lots more....
Ps. I really wanted to release V1.0 at the first of the first of 1996 but
lots of problems popped up and also my life took some twisted turns!!

Version 1.05 (01/03/1997)
-------------------------
New : Online help/guide reader
Minor & Major bug fixes!

Version 1.10-1.20 (31/07/1997)
------------------------------
New : New preferences (lay out) with some new (print) functions!
New : Text style added for albums & songs, also for printing
New : Printer: NLQ/Draft select
New : Printer: Pitch 10, 12 and 17 auto select, 15 and 20 manuel select
New : Add keys : You can now abort the operation
New : Clock alarm!!
New : Text input : Now possible to enter text longer then size of input box
New : Header/Footer: Longer text possible, text style and double width!
Bug fixes:
 -Text input : Delete ALL right from cursor
 -Header/Footer text can be as long as you like <!>
 -Text style : File format change for .MFS and .TPE files
 -Text style : Correct display + scrollers + bar drag
 -Indicator bar now correct when switching between file types
 -No icon is saved (if excists) using Multi update
 -Tape Preferences : Display correct (Disco/Fade time)
 -Window cycle gadget : Mouse pointer correct now
 -A few small bugs

Version 1.30 (09/1997)
----------------------
New:
 -Tools (New version. Used to be external, now internal). Includes: Rename,
  Delete, Makedir, Copy and Relocate.
  Ps. Original Tools version reached V1.02, date 07/97.
 -Auto Assign if MFS: (Volume) is not found
 -Guide viewer, print option now active!
 -Inputing text, special characters use (also) keyboard control
 -Preferences: Due to 'Garbage collection' during printing, Amos forced
  me to use a 'wait' instruction, which will wait according to
  the value set in the preferences.
Changes:
 -Manipulations/Input with auto search for free key,
  Next free key will be searched from the last searched position, not
  number 1 as before. You can abort auto search by hitting one of the
  mouse keys.
 -Serial number removed!
 -From now on only HD support for the program. Inside the program
  you can still use floppies for data storage.
 -Project Icons are now not created from within the program but
  copied from the MFS:Icons/ drawer.
 -Requester if 'Flip to Workbench gadget' is pressed.
 -Flip to Workbench gadget trou-out the program.
Bugs:
 -Buttom margin in Printer options correct.
 -Guide reader nodes. Mem-List big enough now.
 -Tape, save name not in main window.
 -Screen display will now be refreshed after an auto-input manipulation.
 -Question/Volume requester includes HELP key check.
 -Printer prefs: Pitch & Lines now correct.
 -Top Margin error first page removed
 -Header pitch question correct (Now only at first page).
 -Print tape file extended now correct
 -The printer problem with Online/Offline is salved. 
 -Font problem after clock update resolved.
  Display stays correct while scrolling 4x8

Version 1.40 (01/1998)
----------------------
New:
 -New statistics routine. The 'old' one was much to narrow. New window
  layout, new storage system (incompatible with old file style).
  Statistics much more accurate. Supports ANY type of medium!!!
  Data file size smaller. Includes New printing routine.
 -Printer output to file.
  This includes some changes to the preferences menu, a icon for
  the output file and the PrintFiles in the /Tools drawer.
  Now also 'To File' without Printer Escape codes and an information file
  is added.
 -Set style : Range
 -Guide can load/save node list (saves 'lots' of time)
Changes:
 -File write format, from PC format (13,10) to Amiga format (10,-1)
  It also saves disk space, quite a lot of space!!!
 -Input shift+delete and shift+back now without 1/50th of second wait
 -Medium type selection changed. You can make, create and use your
  own types. Changes made to Manipulation/Prefs/Search.
 -Due to new medium types search operation changed a little bit more 
  then average, I thought I should let you know!!
 -Status with guide help reading nodes.
 -Print Help Page/Book: header, footer and buttons now correct 
Bugs:
 -Split function could split 10.000, that's 1 to much, correct now!
 -Preferences bug removed

Version 1.50 (06/1998)
----------------------
New:
 -Samples can only be played in own SMM format.
  Use the NEW converter to convert samples to the SMM format
 -Loader, brandnew routine
 -Ask volume, brandnew routine, comes with loader
 -Text input, routine optimized.
 -2 new programs in tools drawer:
  SampleConvert, convert IFF samples to the SMM format
  SMMplay, a CD player for SMM samples.
 -The song player has been removed
 -The PLAY function in the contents just plays now. No window, no options.
Changes:
 -The normal contents-player has been adapted for use with SMM samples
 -Arrow keys in Manipulations/Changes for going trou the list of
  songs has been sped up a bit. Wait 20 -> Wait 15
 -The time, when a button is pressed, before continuation is sped up
  from 4 to 3 50th of a second
 -Add new keys: Add '100 keys' has been removed and replaced by '???'.
  This means that you can input any number of keys to add to the database.
 -Add new keys: The requester -press right mouse ... - has been changed
  into a display message with the number of keys to be created. Also new
  if the fact that you now can cancel the adding from there, instead of
  only while adding the new keys. *** _YN has been changed:P$="4"/"5" ***
 -Due to lots of bugs in the MEDIUM TYPES I had to make a few changes.
  You can now preset 50 medium types, just like the statistics.
  Also some options have been added. Check it out, the preferences menu.
  I don't like to admit it but I did sloppy work the last time!
 -Medium types in Goto/Search/Manipulations work fine now!
 -ALL filenames now with a maximum of 30 characters
  except Printer filename, set to 20 characters
Bugs:
 -No bar display if database is empty
 -Help: Help restart after error nodes correct now
 -Statistics: Can't create statistics with an empty database
 -Statistics: Display is cleared if you go from a long statistics file
              to a small one.
 -No more blue text when the Alarm clock is active!

Version 1.55 (08/1998)
----------------------
New:
 -FormFeed added to printer prefs (Epson styles is namely GFX based!)
 -Printer spacing added (Not functioning)
Bugs:
 -The input cursor of Manipulations/Erase correct color
 -Loader cursor correct color
 -PPrefs, preferences window leaves other windows alone now
 -Preferences Text lines input box correct
 -Input box Multi new correct display
 -Top Bottom margin printing without doubling escape codes all the time
 -Bottom margin big error: Prefs(5) must be Prefs(7)
 -Footer on/off correct detect while printing
 -No more empty pages if a print job fills pages exactly!
  Ps. This must be one of the oldest bugs ever. I've always had problems
  with this. I think this bug dates back even before CDL!!!!
 -Statistics date now DATE i.s.o. DATA

Version 1.56 (09/1998)
----------------------
Bug fix version
-Fonts now included in MFS:fonts/ and assigned in MFS startup script
-.CFG and .SYS now in (new) settings directory
-Tutor finished and Guide updates
-Assign has been removed and incorperated in the main MFS startup script

Also : @{"  Updates   " link "FUTU"b} 
@endnode
